main event: Two unidentified objects were reported in the sky over Freeville, New York on August 21, 1968, as part of Project Blue Book.
interesting points: The report includes five pages of black and white photographs depicting landscapes with trees and bodies of water., Two dark objects can be seen in the sky of the first photograph., Additional images show light streaks or trails in the sky., The report is part of the Project Blue Book investigations from 1947 to 1969., The documentation comes from the Foreign Technology Division, AFSC, and is marked as UNCLASSIFIED.
sighted object: two unidentified objects in the sky
witness description: no human witnesses identified in the report
